The paper discusses security questions and their implementation, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also focuses on the human aspect of security, specifically on users' behavioural intentions, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the vulnerability of using weak answers to security questions, which is a concern in the field of cybersecurity (cs.CY). The study provides design recommendations for novel security questions mechanisms, which falls under the category of systems and information theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the determinants that influence users' behavioural intentions, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE).
